<br>
 <p><img src=http://members.iinet.net.au/~cornelpm/aandaraa.jpg><BR>Dark Elf Shadow Knight, Sullon Zek Server <BR>Innoruuk claims your SOUL and I will collect it!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/ueljefemariaci.showPublicProfile?language=EN>El Jefe Mariaci</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/21/01 10:42:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Caulfield</span><hr size=1>        Here's what you are missing : The ability to go virtually anywhere you want and camp any dungeon you want. Other than that its the same cept a little monotonous.<br>
<br>
 - el Jefe - <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=FAEBD7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/uagrul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Agrul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tavern Regular</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/22/01 12:54:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Caulfield</span><hr size=1> Well.. I'd say the most interesting thing you're missing is a little experiment a friend of mine (from Tallon Zek) did.<br>
