<A HREF="http://malignant.cjb.net">
<IMG SRC="http://freepages.ugo.com/woohoo/files/MALIGNANT.jpg"></A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/udyensz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DyenSZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/22/01 2:14:55 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.jayartz.com/images/dyen_photo.gif height=182 width=120></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How much am I missing?</span><hr size=1> let me preface this by stating that I haven't played *all* that much on either a blue or red server.<br>
<br>
I find that they each provide a slightly different experience. When playing on a blue server, there is a fairly friendly help everyone kind of attitude (from most people, not all). You will be given stuff and buffed fairly frequently. You can travel wherever you want, including fairly high level dungeons and wait to loot the No Drop item of your desire.<br>
<br>
However, as has been pointed out above, the only *points* seem to be:<br>
<li>socializing<br>
<li>leveling<br>
<li>loot<br>
<br>
On Sullon Zek, the social aspect of the game is very different. You don't find people out to help you (perhaps in part because this is a new server and there aren't the glut of items yet) and I don't find random buffers nearly so often. I think this is because of the danger of the server. It gives an adrenaline rush that I never got on a blue server. But it also makes you keep /anon or /role. And you must conserve your mana so that if you get jumped you can defend yourself.<br>
<br>
On a PvP server, I would say social time has been replaced with tactics and so it is far more challenging and actually requires some skill.<br>
<br>
I would say that if you don't find the game social enough or you feel a lack of loot, try a blue server, otherwise I find Sullon Zek far more exciting and interesting.<br>
<br>
