<br>
pvp advantages: Can kill some PC, only those that arent in your team (Evil, newts, good) Can train if you want to.<br>
<br>
PvE advantages: Can focus more on fighting the more intense NPC, like dragons, gods. Able to travel everywhere and see everything, if you got what it takes.<br>
<br>
<br>
Now that said, i will reply to most of the pro pvp post above, and straighten some things out.<br>
<br>
Wess rainkeeper said: *Well, loot is very easy to come by. My little brother often make new characters on random servers and an hour later they have full bronze and kunark quested weapon*<br>
<br>
I say: Well this is true for both type of game, i dont see how it is not possible on PVP servers? why wouldnt it? SZ was just opened and a week later mostly everyone was full banded, even some in bronze armor and quested, smithed weapons... now some are lvl 55 with much better than that, its worst then blue server imo. After a year that SZ is out, you try and create a newb there, and see what you can get after an hour played....<br>
<br>
Wess also said *Guild politics are very fierce and complicated. High level loot zones are off limits unless you reserved it in advance *<br>
<br>
i say: Once again a point without any logic to it, PVP is the exact thing, and even worst. High level zone are off limits unless your Team is owning it, and if its owned by your team, you will have to do the same as one blue server, train em if you want a certain camp. You wont get a warning for it, but you will get a bad reputation(that you would also get on PvE) and then suffer the consequences.<br>
<br>
Vachir said :*on a blue server it's really just something nice with no real purpose other than to get you to a higher level (so that you can get more gear and level more to get more gear and...). *<br>
<br>
I say: I disagree entirely, getting a runed bone fork on a blue server is just as useful as on a red one, you need to resist spells just as much in order to defeat the greater NPC, or you will be dead in no time, the purpose is the same, resist spell to survive. As for getting higher level and better gear, isnt that the goal of any RPG? isnt that something to look foward too? or do you mean on PVP server you have no need for levels or better gear? Obviously you are not as you were so happy when you got your RBF... and getting level is even MORE important on PVP then PvE, since without them any higher level than you will own you... less they ultra dumb and dont remember how to cast a spell, or hit auto attack...<br>
<br>
He also said *where on SZ, you are trying to get the best stuff you can because it gives you that much better chance at killing rather than being killed*<br>
<br>
I say: Same as on PvE, enough said.<br>
<br>
He added : *Also skill is completely irrelivant, it doesn't matter how effective you are at playing your class, if you're a tank and you can hit things, you're just as good as any other tank, if you're a cleric who keeps people healed, that's just great, if you're a monk who can pull welcome to the club<br>
